1. Configuration Keys and Types
- schedule.supervisor: string enum {off, weekly, daily, hourly, continuous}
  Effect: controls how often the supervisor workflow dispatches. Default in file: "off".
- paths: mapping of artifact names to repository paths (all strings):
  mission -> MISSION.md
  source -> src/lib/
  tests -> tests/unit/
  features -> features/
  library -> library/
  docs -> docs/
  examples -> examples/
  readme -> README.md
  dependencies -> package.json
  contributing -> CONTRIBUTING.md
  library-sources -> SOURCES.md
  Effect: agentic workflows read these paths to locate mission, source, tests and library inputs.
- execution: mapping of commands (strings):
  build -> npm run build
  test -> npm test
  start -> npm run start
  Effect: used by workflows to run build/test/start phases.
- limits: integer settings:
  feature-issues (int) default 2: max concurrent feature issues
  maintenance-issues (int) default 1: max concurrent maintenance issues
  attempts-per-branch (int) default 3
  attempts-per-issue (int) default 2
  features-limit (int) default 2
  library-limit (int) default 32
  Effect: rate-limits agent actions and retries.
- tuning: knobs for agent behavior:
  profile: string {min, recommended, max} default "recommended"
  model: string default "gpt-5-mini" (allowed: gpt-5-mini, claude-sonnet-4, gpt-4.1)
  infinite-sessions: boolean default false
  Optional commented overrides: reasoning-effort, features-scan, source-scan, source-content, issues-scan, document-summary, discussion-comments
  Effect: controls model selection and analysis depth used by automation.
- bot.log-file: string default "intentïon.md" for local agent logs.

