4. Scheduling and Limits (operational behavior)
- supervisor schedule values map to cron-like dispatch frequency used by workflows: off, weekly, daily, hourly, continuous.
- limits.feature-issues caps the number of concurrently open feature issues created by automation.
- attempts-per-issue and attempts-per-branch govern retries; agent implementations must persist attempt counters and avoid exceeding these values.

5. Tuning Options and Effects (practical application)
- model selection affects cost/latency/quality; default gpt-5-mini recommended for balanced runs.
- infinite-sessions=false: agent sessions should compact and terminate; setting true allows longer-lived sessions with compaction concerns.
- source-content (int) controls max chars of source files to include in prompts; use conservative values to avoid prompt truncation.

6. Required Secrets and Permissions (exact names and scopes)
- COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN: create a fine-grained PAT with GitHub Copilot read permission. Purpose: authenticate Copilot SDK for agent tasks.
- WORKFLOW_TOKEN: classic PAT with workflow scope. Purpose: allow init.yml or workflows to update files under .github/workflows/ (GITHUB_TOKEN cannot modify those).
- Repository settings required: Actions allowed, Workflow permissions: Read and write, allow Actions to create PRs, GitHub Discussions enabled for discussions bot.

