8. Update and Install Patterns
- To update agentic infra: npx @xn-intenton-z2a/agentic-lib@latest init
- Use npm install after editing package.json (if adding dependencies)
- Make minimal, targeted changes to distributed files because they are overwritten by agentic-lib init/purge processes; prefer fixes upstream in agentic-lib when applicable.

9. Best Practices (concrete, actionable)
- Keep MISSION.md concise and declarative; automation generates issues from mission text.
- Protect secrets: never commit COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN or WORKFLOW_TOKEN to repo.
- Use branch protection on main: require PR reviews and status checks (select test workflow) before auto-merge.
- Use limits in agentic-lib.toml to throttle automation impact; tune feature-issues and attempts-per-issue conservatively.
- Do not edit distributed files without considering agentic-lib init/purge overwrites; track changes upstream.

10. Troubleshooting (step-by-step)
- Workflow cannot update .github/workflows/: verify WORKFLOW_TOKEN exists with workflow scope; confirm repository Actions permissions allow write.
- Copilot SDK authentication errors: validate COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN scope includes GitHub Copilot read permission and is set in repository secrets.
- Automation creating too many issues: reduce limits.feature-issues and increase attempts-per-issue to reduce noisy retries.
- Tests failing locally: run npm test and inspect tests/unit output. For coverage-enabled unit runs use npm run test:unit.
- Agent sessions exceeding resources: set tuning.infinite-sessions = false and lower source-content limit to reduce prompt sizes.

